honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class AvalancheSettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.AvalancheSettings
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AvalancheSettings
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {AE?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    AIPWhat is the IP address of the Avalanche agent
    ALLShould all data be printed durning a self test.
    ANAWhat is the name of the Avalanche agent
    APTWhat is the port number of the Avalanche agent
    CONType of connection being used to talk to the printer.
    MLNWhat is the printer's model name
    PREIs a prelicensed block being used
    PRNPrinters TCPIP station name
    PRSWhen an Avalanche update is performed this will print out the results if true.
    RUNIs Avalanche support enabled on the printer.
    TTOTCP timeout in milliseconds
    UINUpdate interval in minutes
    UPDFlag is used to tell us how/when the update will be occur
    UTOUDP timeout in milliseconds
    WRDAre we using a wired connection
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • AvalancheSettings

        public AvalancheSettings(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer
